\cf4 \ul \ulc4 Debugging\cf0 \ulnone \
\
A bug in computer programming is an error, failure, or fault in coding. \
Debuggers can identify the exact location or probable cause of a bug in a fraction of the time. \
\
Two major errors that developers can encounter. \
\
\ul 1. Syntax errors\ulnone  = mistakes in 
\f2\i \cf7 how\cf0  
\f0\i0 the code is written (syntax is the format in which programming languages are organized and syntax errors is when the format is violated. )\
\ul 2. Logical errors \ulnone  = mistakes in 
\f2\i \cf7 what\cf0  
\f0\i0 code is written (when a code performs differently than intended.) \
\
Syntax errors on \cf9 HTML browsers are fixed automatically and the fix may result in a different output than intended\cf0 . \
What do they look like in HTML? eg. an opening tag may have no closing tag \
or a declaration may not include the (;) semi colon therefore syntax error would occur. \
\
Logical errors are mistakes in 
\f2\i what
\f0\i0  code is written \
eg. When you use the wrong HTML tag, misspelling text content, Enter an incorrect colour value, or using the wrong property. \
(*** it is important to fix syntax errors before fixing logical errors as it will be difficult to identify obvious logical errors). \
\
\cf10 <h1> 4+4=16 </h1>\cf0  would be an logical error because the plus (+) value should be a multiply (x) value. \
